UNIVERSITY LMS & CRM — ERD (Entity Relationship Diagram)
(Backend: Django — modules: users, courses, assignments, exams, results, finance, attendance, timetable, notifications, library)
 1. USERS MODULE
Tables
User

id (PK)

username

email

password

role (student / teacher / admin / finance)

date_joined

is_active

Student

user_id (FK → User)

registration_no

department

semester

phone

address

Teacher

user_id (FK → User)

designation

department

specialization

Staff

user_id (FK → User)

staff_role

department

Relationships

User 1—1 Student

User 1—1 Teacher

User 1—1 Staff

 2. COURSES MODULE
Course

id (PK)

title

code

department

credit_hours

teacher_id (FK → Teacher)

Module

id (PK)

course_id (FK → Course)

title

Lesson

id (PK)

module_id (FK → Module)

title

description

file (PDF / video / audio)

Enrollment

id (PK)

student_id (FK → Student)

course_id (FK → Course)

status (active, completed, dropped)

Relationships

Course 1—M Module

Module 1—M Lesson

Course M—M Student (via Enrollment)

Course 1—M Teacher

3. ASSIGNMENTS MODULE
Assignment

id (PK)

course_id (FK → Course)

teacher_id (FK → Teacher)

title

description

due_date

Submission

id (PK)

assignment_id (FK → Assignment)

student_id (FK → Student)

file

submitted_at

Grade

id (PK)

submission_id (FK → Submission)

marks

feedback

Relationships

Assignment 1—M Submission

Submission 1—1 Grade

4. EXAMS MODULE
Exam

id

course_id (FK → Course)

title

exam_type (mcq / written)

total_marks

date

QuestionBank

id

exam_id (FK → Exam)

question_text

option_a

option_b

option_c

option_d

correct_answer

ExamAttempt

id

exam_id (FK → Exam)

student_id (FK → Student)

obtained_marks

submitted_at

Relationships

Exam 1—M QuestionBank

Exam 1—M ExamAttempt

Student 1—M ExamAttempt

5. RESULTS MODULE
Result

id

student_id (FK → Student)

course_id (FK → Course)

exam_id (FK → Exam)

total_marks

obtained_marks

grade

Transcript

id

student_id (FK → Student)

cgpa

semester

Relationships

Student 1—M Result

Result M—1 Course

Student 1—1 Transcript

6. FINANCE MODULE
FeeChallan

id

student_id (FK → Student)

amount

due_date

status (paid/unpaid)

Payment

id

challan_id (FK → FeeChallan)

amount

payment_method

payment_date

transaction_id

Scholarship

id

student_id (FK → Student)

percentage

description

Relationships

FeeChallan 1—1/M Payment

Student 1—M FeeChallan

Student 1—M Scholarship

7. NOTIFICATIONS MODULE
Notification

id

user_id (FK → User)

message

type (email/sms/in-app)

status (sent/pending)

8. ATTENDANCE MODULE
Attendance

id

student_id (FK → Student)

course_id (FK → Course)

date

status (present/absent)

Relationships

Student 1—M Attendance

Course 1—M Attendance

9. TIMETABLE MODULE
Timetable

id

course_id (FK → Course)

teacher_id (FK → Teacher)

day

start_time

end_time

room

10. LIBRARY MODULE
Book

id

title

author

isbn

category

copies_available

Issue

id

book_id (FK → Book)

student_id (FK → Student)

issue_date

return_date

Relationships

Book 1—M Issue

Student 1—M Issue

FINAL ERD SUMMARY

Your system has the following relationship structure:

Main Relationships

User → Student/Teacher/Staff (1:1)

Student ↔ Course (M:N via Enrollment)

Course → Module → Lesson (1:M)

Assignment → Submission → Grade (1:M:1)

Exam → Questions → ExamAttempts (1:M:M)

Student → Results → Transcript

Student → FeeChallan → Payment

Student → Attendance

Book → Issue (1:M)